The National Office of the West African Examinations Council (WAEC), Nigeria has announced that it will commence the coordination and marking exercise of the just concluded West African Senior School Certificate Examination (WASSCE) for School Candidates, 2022 on July 13. Mrs. Moyosola Adeyegbe, the Ag. Head, Public Affairs Department of the Council made the announcement in a statement she signed and made available to education journalists on Wednesday. According to hers, the exercise will be carried out at eighty-five (85) marking venues spread across the country. The statement further reads: “To keep up with the practice of releasing candidates’ results 45 days after the conduct of the last paper, the coordination and marking exercise will commence on Wednesday, July 13, 2022, after the Eid-el-Kabir holidays. “The Coordination meetings for Chief Examiners and Team Leaders will be held in the morning of Wednesday, July 13, 2022 while the Assistant Examiners Coordination meetings will commence in the afternoon of the same day. “The coordination meetings would span three days, from Wednesday, July 13 to Friday, July 15, 2022.  This is to enable our Muslim brothers and sisters (Staff and Examiners) to partake fully in the festivities before embarking on the assignment. “The Council wishes to felicitate with the Muslim Ummah on the occasion of the 2022 Eid-El-Kabir celebration”. -Advertisement- POLL 